[
  {
    "text": " ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=2"
  },
  {
    "text": "Hello and welcome to WWDC. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=9"
  },
  {
    "text": "I'm Jeremy Goldman, an engineer on the XCTest team. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=13"
  },
  {
    "text": "In this session, we're going to explore ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=17"
  },
  {
    "text": "some exciting new ways to interact with devices ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=19"
  },
  {
    "text": "from UI Tests in Xcode 13. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=22"
  },
  {
    "text": "In particular, we're going to focus ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=25"
  },
  {
    "text": "on three new interactions ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=27"
  },
  {
    "text": "across three different platforms: ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=28"
  },
  {
    "text": "the iPadOS Pointer, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=31"
  },
  {
    "text": "the watchOS Digital Crown, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=33"
  },
  {
    "text": "and the macOS trackpad.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=35"
  },
  {
    "text": "Let's start with the iPadOS Pointer.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=39"
  },
  {
    "text": "In iPadOS 13.4, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=42"
  },
  {
    "text": "Apple introduced mouse and trackpad support, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=45"
  },
  {
    "text": "providing users with a brand new way ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=48"
  },
  {
    "text": "to interact with iPad, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=49"
  },
  {
    "text": "using accessories like the Magic Keyboard. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=51"
  },
  {
    "text": "Many developers have taken full advantage of this ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=54"
  },
  {
    "text": "by adding pointer-specific behavior and interactions ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=57"
  },
  {
    "text": "to their iPad apps, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=59"
  },
  {
    "text": "like custom hover animations. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=61"
  },
  {
    "text": "In Xcode 13, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=63"
  },
  {
    "text": "we're providing a powerful new API ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=65"
  },
  {
    "text": "for controlling the iPadOS Pointer in UI Tests. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=67"
  },
  {
    "text": "This API will enable you to create robust automated tests ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=71"
  },
  {
    "text": "for multiple types of pointer interactions ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=75"
  },
  {
    "text": "in your iPad apps ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=78"
  },
  {
    "text": "and will be available for use ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=79"
  },
  {
    "text": "with devices running iPadOS 15 and later.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=81"
  },
  {
    "text": "Let's examine this new API in more detail. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=85"
  },
  {
    "text": "First, we're adding a new property on XCUIDevice ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=88"
  },
  {
    "text": "to indicate whether or not ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=92"
  },
  {
    "text": "a device supports pointer interaction. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=93"
  },
  {
    "text": "Next, we're adding new methods on XCUIElement ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=97"
  },
  {
    "text": "for performing different pointer interactions, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=101"
  },
  {
    "text": "like hovering, multiple types of clicking, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=103"
  },
  {
    "text": "and two-finger scrolling. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=106"
  },
  {
    "text": "We're also adding methods ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=109"
  },
  {
    "text": "for more advanced click-and-drag use cases ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=110"
  },
  {
    "text": "as well as a class method for executing blocks of code ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=113"
  },
  {
    "text": "with one or more modifier keys held down. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=116"
  },
  {
    "text": "These methods are also available on XCUICoordinate, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=120"
  },
  {
    "text": "if additional precision is required. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=123"
  },
  {
    "text": "Let's explore how these new APIs work in practice ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=126"
  },
  {
    "text": "by creating a new UI Test for a pointer interaction ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=129"
  },
  {
    "text": "in an iOS app.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=132"
  },
  {
    "text": "In this demo, I'll be using the Fruta app, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=134"
  },
  {
    "text": "which has a sidebar ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=136"
  },
  {
    "text": "that's initially hidden on launch. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=137"
  },
  {
    "text": "I recently added pointer-specific functionality ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=140"
  },
  {
    "text": "on iPad, where a horizontal two-finger trackpad swipe ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=142"
  },
  {
    "text": "opens the sidebar. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=146"
  },
  {
    "text": "Let's add a UI Test for that. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=148"
  },
  {
    "text": "Here I have an empty UI Test class, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=151"
  },
  {
    "text": "which is where I'll add my new UI Test.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=153"
  },
  {
    "text": "Let's quickly walk through what this test is doing. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=158"
  },
  {
    "text": "It starts by launching the app ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=162"
  },
  {
    "text": "and then asserting that the sidebar ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=164"
  },
  {
    "text": "is not initially present on launch. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=166"
  },
  {
    "text": "Then it performs a horizontal two-finger trackpad swipe ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=169"
  },
  {
    "text": "and asserts that the sidebar is now present. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=173"
  },
  {
    "text": "One other thing I'd like to point out ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=176"
  },
  {
    "text": "is this availability attribute ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=178"
  },
  {
    "text": "I've added on the test method. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=180"
  },
  {
    "text": "This is necessary whenever you're using methods ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=182"
  },
  {
    "text": "that are only available starting with a specific iOS version. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=184"
  },
  {
    "text": "In this case, the pointer interaction APIs ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=188"
  },
  {
    "text": "were introduced in iOS 15.0.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=191"
  },
  {
    "text": "Let's try running the test on the iPad simulator. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=194"
  },
  {
    "text": "You can follow along with the cursor indicator, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=197"
  },
  {
    "text": "which is the dark circle ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=200"
  },
  {
    "text": "near the bottom left corner of the screen. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=201"
  },
  {
    "text": " ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=204"
  },
  {
    "text": "Great! It looks like our test works on iPad. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=224"
  },
  {
    "text": "However, this app is also available on iPhone, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=227"
  },
  {
    "text": "which does not support pointer interaction. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=230"
  },
  {
    "text": "Let's try running this test on the iPhone simulator. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=233"
  },
  {
    "text": " ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=236"
  },
  {
    "text": "So it appears the test failed ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=250"
  },
  {
    "text": "with an error message that ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=253"
  },
  {
    "text": "\"Pointer events are not supported on this device.\" ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=254"
  },
  {
    "text": "To resolve this, we need to modify our test ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=258"
  },
  {
    "text": "so that it only executes on devices ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=260"
  },
  {
    "text": "that do support pointer interaction. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=262"
  },
  {
    "text": "We can do this by using ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=265"
  },
  {
    "text": "XCTSkipUnless with the new ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=266"
  },
  {
    "text": "supportsPointerInteraction property on XCUIDevice ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=268"
  },
  {
    "text": "to skip the test on unsupported devices, instead of failing. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=272"
  },
  {
    "text": " ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=276"
  },
  {
    "text": "Now let's try running the test on the iPhone simulator again. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=281"
  },
  {
    "text": " ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=284"
  },
  {
    "text": "Perfect. So now this test will be skipped ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=290"
  },
  {
    "text": "on devices that don't support pointer interaction. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=292"
  },
  {
    "text": "Let's talk about some new ways ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=296"
  },
  {
    "text": "to interact with devices on other platforms, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=298"
  },
  {
    "text": "more specifically, watchOS and the Digital Crown. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=301"
  },
  {
    "text": "As you may already know, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=305"
  },
  {
    "text": "Xcode 12.5 introduced UI Testing support ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=307"
  },
  {
    "text": "for watchOS apps. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=310"
  },
  {
    "text": "This support includes methods newly available on watchOS ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=312"
  },
  {
    "text": "for synthesizing touch events ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=316"
  },
  {
    "text": "as well as hardware button events, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=318"
  },
  {
    "text": "like clicking the crown.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=319"
  },
  {
    "text": "In Xcode 13, we're expanding this support ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=322"
  },
  {
    "text": "with a new method ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=325"
  },
  {
    "text": "for synthesizing Digital Crown rotation. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=326"
  },
  {
    "text": "This method requires just one parameter, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=329"
  },
  {
    "text": "the number of rotations, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=332"
  },
  {
    "text": "and has an optional velocity parameter ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=334"
  },
  {
    "text": "to specify the speed at which the crown should be rotated. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=336"
  },
  {
    "text": "This velocity parameter has type XCUIGestureVelocity, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=340"
  },
  {
    "text": "which means you can either use one of the preset values, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=344"
  },
  {
    "text": "like slow, fast, and default, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=347"
  },
  {
    "text": "or you can specify a custom decimal value ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=350"
  },
  {
    "text": "in rotations per second.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=352"
  },
  {
    "text": "Let's see how this new method works in practice.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=355"
  },
  {
    "text": "Say I have a simple weather app for watchOS ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=359"
  },
  {
    "text": "that displays the current temperature outside. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=361"
  },
  {
    "text": "The app has a feature ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=364"
  },
  {
    "text": "where users can scroll the digital crown forward ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=365"
  },
  {
    "text": "to see forecasted temperatures at future times ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=368"
  },
  {
    "text": "or scroll backward ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=371"
  },
  {
    "text": "to see the recorded temperature at past times.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=372"
  },
  {
    "text": "Let's walk through a basic UI Test ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=376"
  },
  {
    "text": "that makes sure this crown rotation functionality ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=378"
  },
  {
    "text": "behaves as expected.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=380"
  },
  {
    "text": "The test starts by launching the app ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=382"
  },
  {
    "text": "and then asserting that the forecast time label ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=385"
  },
  {
    "text": "initially says Current Temperature. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=387"
  },
  {
    "text": "Then, we rotate the digital crown one full rotation forward, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=390"
  },
  {
    "text": "and assert the label updated to say \"One hour from now.\" ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=394"
  },
  {
    "text": "After that, we rotate the crown two full rotations backward, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=398"
  },
  {
    "text": "and the test finishes by asserting ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=402"
  },
  {
    "text": "that the label updated to say \"One hour ago.\" ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=404"
  },
  {
    "text": "Finally, let's talk about the macOS trackpad. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=408"
  },
  {
    "text": "More specifically, let's focus on scrolling. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=412"
  },
  {
    "text": "Scrolling can be broken down into two different categories: ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=415"
  },
  {
    "text": "discrete and continuous. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=419"
  },
  {
    "text": "Discrete scrolling has precise incremental movement. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=421"
  },
  {
    "text": "Think about rotating the scroll wheel ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=425"
  },
  {
    "text": "on a physical mouse. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=427"
  },
  {
    "text": "The on-screen content moves in uniform increments ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=429"
  },
  {
    "text": "for each tick on the scroll wheel, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=432"
  },
  {
    "text": "and the movement is non-inertial, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=434"
  },
  {
    "text": "meaning it stops moving immediately ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=436"
  },
  {
    "text": "when you stop rotating the scroll wheel. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=438"
  },
  {
    "text": "On the other hand, continuous, or phased scrolling, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=441"
  },
  {
    "text": "has fluid and dynamic movement. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=445"
  },
  {
    "text": "Picture swiping with two fingers on a trackpad. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=447"
  },
  {
    "text": "The on-screen content ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=450"
  },
  {
    "text": "scrolls smoothly while you're swiping, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=452"
  },
  {
    "text": "and the movement is inertial, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=453"
  },
  {
    "text": "meaning it continues moving after you lift your fingers off ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=455"
  },
  {
    "text": "until it gradually comes to a stop.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=458"
  },
  {
    "text": "XCTest currently provides a scroll method on macOS ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=462"
  },
  {
    "text": "that enables you to perform discrete pixel-precise scrolling ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=466"
  },
  {
    "text": "in your UI Tests. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=469"
  },
  {
    "text": "This method requires two parameters ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=471"
  },
  {
    "text": "to specify the exact horizontal and vertical distance ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=473"
  },
  {
    "text": "in pixels to scroll.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=477"
  },
  {
    "text": "In Xcode 13, we're introducing new methods ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=481"
  },
  {
    "text": "for synthesizing continuous or trackpad-like scrolling ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=484"
  },
  {
    "text": "on macOS. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=487"
  },
  {
    "text": "These methods accept an optional velocity parameter ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=489"
  },
  {
    "text": "to specify the speed at which you'd like to scroll. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=492"
  },
  {
    "text": "This velocity parameter has type XCUIGestureVelocity ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=496"
  },
  {
    "text": "which means, just like in ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=500"
  },
  {
    "text": "the rotateDigitalCrown method we explored earlier, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=501"
  },
  {
    "text": "you can either use the presets ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=504"
  },
  {
    "text": "or you can specify a custom decimal value ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=506"
  },
  {
    "text": "in pixels per second.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=508"
  },
  {
    "text": "Xcode 13 introduces APIs across multiple platforms ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=511"
  },
  {
    "text": "to enable automation of new input methods ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=516"
  },
  {
    "text": "and provide support for more specialized use cases.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=518"
  },
  {
    "text": "Use this new functionality to create UI Tests ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=523"
  },
  {
    "text": "for pointer-specific interactions in your iPad apps, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=526"
  },
  {
    "text": "automate digital crown rotation in your watchOS UI Tests, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=530"
  },
  {
    "text": "and perform continuous, trackpad-like scrolling on macOS ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=534"
  },
  {
    "text": "with the new swipe methods. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=537"
  },
  {
    "text": "If you're interested in learning more, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=540"
  },
  {
    "text": "make sure to check out these related sessions.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=541"
  },
  {
    "text": "Thanks for watching and enjoy the rest of WWDC. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=545"
  },
  {
    "text": "[music]",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10208/?time=549"
  }
]